			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-533984">
									

<p>Perhaps s/he could change it to something like "expels a chunk of tissue, which examination has thus far revealed to be that of a human (kidney/liver) in a state consistent with recent death from severe dehydration?" Something unrecognizable at first sight, maybe chunked so it'd fit into the filter, but that actually has something to do with filtration. And you might still hear the pulse if it was, say, a spatially displaced coring of some living person's liver/kidney/whatever. Kidney would fit best, but I like liver, if only because it's harder to identify at first glance. Unless you're fairly familiar with the appearance of the human liver, in which case you go, "Hey, who put a chunk of human liver in my water filter?"</p>

